bio: As a refugee child, Assal was often made to feel like she had to prove herself more than others. But her mother always taught her about the power of being herself. A former weightlifter and police officer, she’s learned that true strength is both vulnerability and the ability to get comfortable in the discomfort of hard work. Because a strong body starts with a strong mindset. Now, she’s bringing her passion, precision, dedication, and drive to classes that will motivate you to strengthen your muscles and your mind. She wants to show you that the only person you need to prove anything to is yourself—and that once you embrace this, you’ll be unstoppable.
short_bio: A former weightlifter and police officer, Assal Arian knows that a strong body starts with a strong mindset. She wants to show you that the only person you need to prove anything to is yourself—once you embrace this, you’ll be unstoppable.
background: I’ve been told I’m too ambitious, too small, too Persian. But it just made me stronger, because my mum showed me the power of being me. And this is what I teach in my classes—the only person you need to prove anything to is yourself.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate others?', 'There is so much power in being a beginner—when you’re ready and motivated to learn is when you really grow. I make my classes a place where everyone feels empowered to try new things and see what they can achieve.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I love music. Any kind of music. From reggaeton to hip hop, house, electro to dancehall and flamenco. It helps me lose myself in the moment and find motivation in different places.'], ['', '']]
quote: I’m always trying something new, finding new challenges, getting out of my comfort zone, and working to improve.
name: Assal Arian

bio: Hailing from Tampico, Mexico, Mariana grew up in a family full of athletes who drew on each other’s hard work and discipline to succeed. But as she grew older, her passion for teaching became evident as she loved helping others find their inner strength. A yoga teacher for over 11 years, Mariana has taught bilingual classes from Mexico City to NYC. Her classes are a mix of warmth, tough love and infectious energy. Her goal is to make you both smile and sweat.
short_bio: Hailing from Tampico, Mexico, Mariana will draw you to her empowering light with Spanish and English classes. With a competitive athletic background, movement, breath, energy and compassion are a huge part of Mariana’s practice.
background: I love when someone who is maybe a bit resistant to yoga takes class and feels they got as much of a workout as they did during a run, Bike ride, floor class.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'I try to approach with an open heart, open mind and shining heart.'], ['Outside of Peloton? ', 'Outside of Peloton, you can catch Mariana waiting in line to see the latest play or running and reading in Central Park. '], ['', '']]
name: Mariana Fernández

bio: Kendall is a natural-born fighter who empowers you to find your voice and believe in your inner strength. Kendall is a dynamic athlete, with a background in professional cheerleading, gymnastics, dance and boxing. After college, Kendall began what she believed would be a dream job at a tech startup, but soon realized the culture wasn’t the right fit for her. To cope, Kendall began boxing, where she discovered that her true calling is empowering others to break down barriers through movement and sweat. In her classes, Kendall uses the power of positive energy and rock 'n' roll to inspire you to rise up and discover your highest self.
short_bio: Kendall is a natural-born fighter who empowers you to believe in your inner strength. As a dynamic athlete, coach and creative, Kendall uses the power of positive energy to inspire you to rise up and commit to your highest self.
background: My goal is to help you discover your power. We have a choice when it comes to listening to the voice in our heads: it holds us back or helps us rise up. It just depends on how we train it.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'POSITIVE ENERGY! What we put out in the world comes back to us, so there is no time for negativity. We are all in this together for support and accountability, and I hope you enter my class feeling curious and proud.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I am a boxer at heart and have been learning the art for over 7 years. Rock ‘n’ roll seeps through my soul, especially the classics, so you can also find me listening to vinyl or scrounging up tickets to a show. '], ['', '']]
quote: Rise up and greet your higher self
name: Kendall Toole

bio: Jenn Sherman took her first indoor cycling class more than a decade ago and was instantly hooked. As Peloton’s very first cycling instructor, Jenn came to NYC from her hometown in New Jersey, where she’d been selling out studios for years. Jenn brings a focused intensity to every class she teaches, showing Members what they’re made of with her empowering playlists you just can’t help but sing along to.
short_bio: "JFDI!!! Or (JUST F**KING DO IT) No excuses. Simple, direct and to the point. Just like ME!"
music_bio: Check out a sample of Jenn's current class playlist.
background: Being able to make a difference in people’s lives is the inspiration. I draw from the strength, motivation and the incredible energy I receive every day from my riders.
ordered_q_and_as:
[['How Do You Motivate?
', 'Leave the bulls**t outside the door and take this window of time for YOU. Walk in ready to work hard, sweat hard, sing hard and leave the room feeling empowered by what you just accomplished.'], ['Outside of Peloton
', 'I am the mom to two teenagers, who are the center of my world. When I’m not running in circles with my family, I can be found relaxing at the beach with friends, or working on my next killer playlist.
'], ['', '']]
quote: JFDI!!! Or (JUST F**KING DO IT) No excuses. Simple, direct and to the point. Just like ME!
name: Jenn Sherman

bio:
When Susie’s brother convinced her to enter a half-marathon, it signalled a remarkable turning point for her. Previously more often found partying than PB-ing, Susie’s gone on to become one of the most recognisable faces in the British running community, a four-time Marathon des Sables finisher and a world record-breaker for treadmill running.
It’s no wonder she believes everyone can be a runner, setting you up for success by focussing on technique, comfort and ticking off achievable goals, regardless of your age or ability. This wickedly funny Brit is all about helping you be the best version of yourself today.
short_bio: Susie sets you up for success by focussing on your technique and comfort and helping you tick off achievable goals. Because she believes everyone can be a runner, this wickedly funny Brit helps you be the best version of yourself today.
background: I believe running is for everyone. From my own experience, I know that with a little bit of self-belief, combined with the magic of putting one foot in front of the other, anything is possible. I’m here to get you to where you want to be.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate? ', 'Being the best version of yourself on the day is all you can be. If you come to push yourself, to move or to have fun, I’ve got your back, and you’ll leave with a smile on your face.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'My family, my dogs and travelling are my favourite things … and of course running! Spare time at home is spent exploring the trails with my friends. Downtime is spent reading, cooking and eating.'], ['', '']]
quote: DON'T BE DEFINED BY OTHER PEOPLE'S EXPECTATIONS. DEFINE YOUR OWN STRENGTHS.
name: Susie Chan

bio: As a model, dancer, certified health coach, host of the Brooklyn Nets, runner, and the founder of fitness lifestyle brand Love Squad, Ally really does it all. At Peloton as in all of her pursuits, Ally’s goal is to lead by example while empowering people to approach wellness and fitness in a positive light. When she’s not on the Peloton Bike, you can find her flexing her entrepreneurial muscles, or enjoying a good doughnut.
short_bio: They say the early bird gets the worm, but the early bird only gets whatever is left over from the hustlers.
music_bio: Check out a sample of Ally’s current class playlist.
background: My life goal is to remind the world that we all have one life to live, and together we should live it to the fullest. I believe that what connects us most is the power of sweat, and physically working through things as a team.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'We ride to become boss of the Bike and to remind ourselves that we are the boss of our lives. My classes are designed to make you feel proud and uplifted, both on and off the bike.'], ['Outside of Peloton', "I always try find the right balance of fun and work, knowing they don't have to be different things. Off the Bike I love donuts, tennis, basketball, karaoke and parties."], ['', '']]
quote: They say the early bird gets the worm, but the early bird only gets whatever is left over from the hustlers.
name: Ally Love

bio: If there’s one thing Marcel cares about, it’s that you have fun during his classes and harness your inner power. The former soccer player has learned that giving back, supporting others and being present in the moment is much more powerful than any victory. In his classes, you can expect lots of motivation and positive vibes, as well as Marcel’s contagious smile.
short_bio: Marcel wants you to have fun during your workout. The former soccer player firmly believes that giving back, supporting others and being present in the moment is much more powerful than any victory. Celebrate every workout with him.
background: Soccer has been my passion ever since I can remember. I’ve taken all that fun, that spirit and the experiences of the game with me on my journey.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I want to help you find your inner power. But most importantly, I want you to have fun. Let’s celebrate every workout together!'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I try to be present in every moment, and instead of my successes, I celebrate my experiences—walks with my girlfriend and our dog Hugo, travels or football games. My vice is ice cream. I have at least one every day.'], ['', '']]
name: Marcel Maurer

bio: When Anna first turned to yoga, she felt a switch turn on inside of her. As she built a deeper connection with her mind and body, she began accomplishing things she never knew possible. Moved to share the transformative properties of the practice with others, Anna dove head first into yoga. Anna has crafted a unique teaching style that uses movement and music to help her Members connect to the same healing properties of yoga that she has experienced over the years. Anna is a prominent teacher trainer, workshop leader and instructor in NYC.
short_bio: “Look for balance but always be willing to fall”
background: My classes combine heat building movement with precise, focused instruction for Members to find stability and space in their bodies and minds. Watching Members grow and thrive on the mat and in their lives is what inspires me to teach!
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I aim to inspire people to do their best and let go of the results. Yoga is not a competition or performance, it’s just for you (how great is that?). It’s a tool to strengthen your relationship with yourself.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'When I’m not standing on my hands, you can catch me traveling the world whenever, and wherever I can. I enjoy being in nature, hiking, biking and just walking around and taking it all in.'], ['', '']]
quote: Look for balance but always be willing to fall.
name: Anna Greenberg

bio: Peloton’s VP of Fitness Programming, Robin believes that sweat transforms lives. Her journey to Peloton came after she literally ran herself out of a successful law career. Robin is passionate about guiding Members past their limitations and excuses with inspiring, authentic anecdotes. Author of the New York Times bestseller Shut Up and Run, Robin is a RRCA-certified running coach and ultramarathoner. Her life’s mission is to redefine and rethink possibility through movement.
music_bio: Ready to ride? Check out a sample of Robin's current class playlist.
background: A life lived in sweat is my mission. Every day, I work hard planting seeds for tomorrow’s greatness. The hustle in me honors the hustle in you.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'With a heavy dose of tough love because iron sharpens iron. The pride of hard work lasts longer than the discomfort. And no matter what, just keep showing up.'], ['Outside of Peloton', ' Always searching for the next best sweat, you can catch me adding up miles and increasing reps around New York City and beyond.'], ['', '']]
name: Robin Arzón

bio: Kirsten welcomes runners of all levels in her motivating classes. A successful career woman turned fitness instructor, Kirsten wholeheartedly embraces the changes that life brings. After seven years of working with the NFL, she shifted her focus to family. Her journey to motherhood was not easy, and fitness helped Kirsten strengthen her body and soul during difficult times. She is now the proud mother of two beautiful daughters and uses her life experiences to fuel her deeply inspiring workouts. Get lifted with Kirsten as you run together to the beats of her favorite hip hop and R&B tracks.
background: My goal in every class is to remind you that you are more than enough. If it is on your heart to do it, that means you have already been called to it. You just have to take that step, and I’ll be here right alongside you.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'Come as you! I coach from a place of learning from past experiences. We get comfortable in the uncomfortable. Let go of the idea of perfection and embrace your uniqueness.That is your superpower! You are a warrior. '], ['Outside of Peloton?', 'You can find me being a silly mom with my two daughters. Currently, singing and dance parties are our thing. When the babies are asleep, I’m at the gym or listening to the most ratchet music I can find.'], ['', '']]
quote: “Don’t let anyone dim your light. You were born to shine, baby!”
name: Kirsten Ferguson

bio: Tunde’s mission is to inspire and motivate other people to believe in the impossible. After years of struggling with her weight and self-confidence, Tunde fell in love with fitness and the doors it opened for her. Through a career as a celebrity makeup artist and brand educator, she discovered that she had a knack for teaching others to feel empowered and strong. Tunde brings an unparalleled positive energy to the Bike, fueled by personal experiences, perseverance and powerful playlists. There’s no doubt you’ll leave her classes feeling on top of the world.
short_bio: Tunde’s mission is to inspire and motivate other people to believe in the impossible. After overcoming challenging life experiences, Tunde radiates positivity and perseverance from the inside out.
background: I focus on crafting my classes with music that drives you. This rush of adrenaline allows you to move past the expectations or limitations you showed up with that day. Beyond that, I will always push you, but never let you fall.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', "I motivate from experience. I'm on a forever journey, and have been in your shoes before. I will always push you, because I know you can come up from where you are, even if you haven’t fully realized it yet. "], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I’m from Texas, so Tex-Mex and margaritas have a special place in my heart. The beach is my happy place, laughing is my favorite thing to do and I’ll never turn down the chance to strut across a dance floor! '], ['', '']]
quote: Embrace the beauty of uncertainty. It’s a place of infinite possibility.
name: Tunde Oyeneyin

bio: Andy takes a technique-centered approach to fitness, drawing on his experience as an accomplished former gymnast and pole vaulter in his home state of Connecticut. A celebrated personal trainer in NYC before joining Peloton, Andy is inspired by the world-class fitness and strength coaches who taught him, and brings his breadth of training knowledge to every workout.
background: My inspiration for teaching is rooted in helping others improve their lives through fitness, as other coaches have done for me, now it’s my turn to pay it forward.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I want members to approach my class with an intent to be challenged and grow. I focus on technique and ensure that there is a purpose behind everything I ask of you.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'My training also includes gymnastics, kettlebells, Olympic weightlifting, Muay Thai kickboxing, and yoga. I also enjoy watching documentaries, meditation, reading, and listening to Podcasts.'], ['', '']]
name: Andy Speer

bio: Growing up in Hamburg, Cliff’s first love was football–until music came along. In fact, his love of hip hop saw him become the first German rapper to make it to the semi-finals of the ‘Voice of Germany’. Given he’s used to performing on a stage under the bright lights, it’s no wonder he feels so at home in the Peloton studio. As a Peloton Instructor, Cliff’s passion and energy mean you leave his class not only feeling like you’ve had a great workout, but also feeling re-energised and ready to hit all the high notes. Cliff rides in our London studio and does Bike and Bootcamp classes in German.
short_bio: As a Peloton Instructor, Cliff’s passion and energy help you leave his class not only feeling like you’ve had a great workout, but also being re-energised and ready to take on whatever life has in store for you.
background: I’m inspired by the synergy of music and fitness, it gives me an energy that I just have to pass on. Everyone feels that in every single class I give.
ordered_q_and_as: [['HOW DO YOU MOTIVATE?', 'As an athlete, praise and positive encouragement have always driven me to push myself beyond my limits and perform at my best. With this power, I want to motivate everyone to achieve more and look for fewer excuses. '], ['OUTSIDE OF PELOTON', "When I'm not on the Peloton stage, I spend as much time as possible with my family. My wife and daughter mean everything to me."], ['', '']]
quote: No excuses - Don't look for excuses, find solutions.
name: Cliff Dwenger

bio:
Marcel is an exceptional athlete with a background in basketball, track and field and cross country. Her time in the Army propelled her to unlock her true strength through structure and discipline. She uses this knowledge to empower her students of all levels—from the beginner to the experienced runner.

Marcel’s classes are exhilarating. Music powers her workouts, and trap and pop beats drive each interval. Marcel will motivate you as you run together to reach your next goal.
background: I aim to empower and inspire in everything that I do. That’s my mission.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'I live for a good challenge. I want Members to know that they don’t have to show up with all the answers but feel confident that together, as one unit, we will be relentless in ensuring they get across the finish line.'], ['Outside of Peloton?', 'I love movement. A bike ride through the borough, a hike upstate or even a walk through the park—I love being outdoors. I also love catching up with my closest friends and family to recharge and refill my cup.'], ['', '']]
name: Marcel Dinkins

bio: Emma Lovewell is a Martha’s Vineyard native and a woman of all trades. She’s spent much of her career in fitness and wellness as a professional dancer, dance coach, fitness model, personal trainer and pilates instructor. Emma was also a DJ, and brings this love of music to her teaching style at Peloton. She’s passionate about movement and connecting the heavy beats of her playlists to each ride she teaches. After class, expect to feel like you just stepped off the dance floor.
short_bio: "I love you, but I’m going to push you."
music_bio: Check out a sample of Emma’s current class playlist.
background: I always try to find the perfect combination of training and entertainment so that class will fly by, and you won’t even realize how hard you just pushed yourself.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I want people to feel lighter when they finish my class; whether it’s leaving behind a puddle of sweat, or letting go of negative thoughts or feelings. Don’t ever miss an opportunity to get stronger.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I come from a creative family of entrepreneurs so I play the piano, enjoy painting watercolors, cooking, gardening, adventuring and traveling. I always need a creative outlet so I have a lot of hobbies!'], ['', '']]
quote: I love you, but I’m going to push you.
name: Emma Lovewell
